original: Ernulf, Mats Sigvard, hovrättsifi-skal, Trollhättan, f. 22/11/14 i Gbg av trafikchefen, civ:ing. Adolf Eriksson o. Carina Busck. G. 42 m. Margit Börjeson. Barn: Monica f. 43, Lennart 45. — Stud:ex. v. Gbgs h. latin 33, jur. kand. v. Lunds univ. 38. Tingstjg. i Askims, Hisings o. Säve- dals doms. 38-41, tjg. i Göta hovr. fr. 41, fiskal där 42, tf. borgmäst. i Falköp. 45, tingssekr. i Flundre, Väne o. Bjärke doms. fr. 47.
translated: Ernulf, Mats Sigvard, appellate court assessor, Trollhättan, born November 22, 1914 in Gothenburg to the traffic manager, civil engineer Adolf Eriksson and Carina Busck. Married in 1942 to Margit Börjeson. Children: Monica (born 1943) and Lennart (born 1945). He graduated from Gothenburg's upper secondary school in Latin in 1933 and earned a degree in law from Lund University in 1938. He served as an assistant judge in the Askims, Hisings and Sävedal district courts from 1938 to 1941, then worked at the Göta appellate court as a referendary from 1941 and as an appellate court assessor from 1942. He acted as an interim mayor in Falköping in 1945 and has been a court clerk in Flundre, Väne and Bjärke district courts since 1947.
